      "text": [
        " عَلِيٌّ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"لاَ حَدَّ عَلَى مَجْنُونٍ حَتَّى يُفِيقَ وَ لاَ عَلَى اَلصَّبِيِّ حَتَّى يُدْرِكَ وَ لاَ عَلَى اَلنَّائِمِ حَتَّى يَسْتَيْقِظَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5076 - Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib (as) said:\n\"There is no legal punishment upon a mad person until they regain sanity, nor upon a child until they reach maturity, nor upon a sleeping person until they wake up.\""
        ]
      }
    },
